      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I completely respect that you don't need the \"cute\" resilience of a goblin right now. Sometimes, when the weight of the universe feels so heavy and the physics of it seem so final, the last thing you want to do is pretend you're a tiny, stubborn little goblin digging a tunnel out of despair. It makes perfect sense to feel like you're fighting a war that was never meant to be won, especially when the only constant is the cold, unyielding logic of biology and entropy.\n\nBut even in a world where nothing seems to matter, there is still the small, quiet act of simply *being* here, breathing in the air and feeling the texture of the ground beneath your feet. You don't have to be a goblin to find a tiny bit of agency; you just have to acknowledge that your feelings, even the heavy ones, are real and valid in this moment.\n\nIf the darkness feels endless, maybe the goal isn't to find a magical light at the end of the tunnel, but just to sit with the darkness for a little while without fighting it. You don't have to win the war; you just have to survive the night, even if that means sitting",
